Remarks: In the Mediterranean region,
Oenopia conglobata
is among the most common lady beetle found in residential areas (
Lumbierres et al . 2018
). This species was collected from almond trees infested with aphids in 90% of the localities visited. Intraguild predation between
Coccinella septempunctata
and
Oenopia conglobata
was observed on almond trees. Trees were dominated by one species or the other but not both. However,
Coccinella
consistently preyed on the
Oenopia
larvae.
